SIMPLE: persistent
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Persistent
<hw>Per*sist"ent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>persistens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of
<ets>persistere</ets>. See <er>Persist</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Inclined to persist; having staying qualities; tenacious of
position or purpose.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Remaining beyond the period when
parts of the same kind sometimes fall off or are absorbed; permanent;
<as>as, <ex>persistent</ex> teeth or gills; a <ex>persistent</ex>
calyx</as>; -- opposed to <contr>deciduous</contr>, and
<contr>caducous</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Persistently</ent>⟦br⟧
